{{notable|date=February 2014}}
The '''Einaudi Institute for Economics and Finance''' (EIEF) is a [[Rome]] based economics research institute, funded by the [[Banca d'Italia|Bank of Italy]]. 

The Institute builds on the tradition of its predecessor, the Ente Luigi Einaudi, that has fostered economic research in Italy for the past fifty years.{{cn|date=February 2014}}

The Einaudi Institute for Economics and Finance produces research, with an emphasis on policy relevant topics. It also seeks to influence public thinking and to train the next generation of scholars by running seminar series, graduate level courses and conferences. 

==External links==
* [http://www.eief.it EIEF Official Website]
