{{term|term= '''[[Cell membrane]]'''}}{{defn|defn=The '''cell membrane''' (also known as the '''plasma membrane''' or '''cytoplasmic membrane,''' and historically referred to as the '''plasmalemma''') is a [[biological membrane]] that separates the [[cytoplasm|interior]] of all [[Cell (biology)|cells]] from the [[extracellular space|outside environment]] (the extracellular space) which protects the cell from its environment<ref>[http://users.rcn.com/jkimball.ma.ultranet/BiologyPages/C/CellMembranes.html Kimball's Biology pages] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125224255/http://users.rcn.com/jkimball.ma.ultranet/BiologyPages/C/CellMembranes.html |date=2009-01-25 }}, Cell Membranes</ref><ref>{{cite book |author1=Singleton P |title=Bacteria in Biology, Biotechnology and Medicine |edition=5th |isbn=978-0-471-98880-9 |year=1999 |publisher=Wiley |location=New York}}</ref> consisting of a [[lipid bilayer]] with embedded [[protein]]s.}}
